Marc (The Mouth of Odin) – Singer/songwriter/guitarist and founder of Odin’s Other Eye.  Marc is a simple mortal conduit for the words of Odin.  He prepares the rest of the band for the 2nd coming…

Nathan (Odin’s thunder) – Oft seen in kilt on stage, bassist Nathan reps the jazz element for the group.  His background is more obscure and we are reluctant to ask questions…

Matt (Odin’s lightning) – Whether via axe, flute, violin, cello, harp or other random instrument that crosses his path, Matt opens the doorway to Odin’s new progressive venture…

Paul (Odin’s drummer boy) – Odin’s original drummer returns!  Easily capable of crushing small children, Paul has a heavy hand and an interesting meter.  Please welcome him back to the stage!

Odin’s eye is the sun that burns bright in the sky.  His other eye, of course, is the moon, and a full moon is an auspicious occasion.  Odin hosts special quarterly events – rock concerts and masquerade balls, complete with pagan vendors and random artists.
